{
  "doc_id": "5128",
  "text": "In cirrhotic patients, serum CysC concentrations may also be a good marker for prognosis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Our previous study has shown that CysC levels significantly correlated with MELD scoring system, suggesting that it should be a good marker for assessing the prognosis in these patients [CITATION_3] . However, prognostic usefulness of serum CysC concentrations in HBV-ACLF patients has not been investigated previously. Thus, the study was aimed to evaluate whether serum CysC levels were associated with mortality, and further develop a new prognostic index to estimate the survival in patients with HBV-ACLF.",
